To compile ffmpeg for Windows or Mac OS X follow the steps below, note that
for Linux the livavcodec-dev, libavformat-dev, libavutil-dev and
libswscale-dev packages should be installed instead.

Mac OS X:
- Make sure XCode is installed and start a terminal.

- Extract the libexif sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- Configure ffmpeg using:
  ./configure --disable-ffmpeg --disable-ffplay --disable-ffprobe --disable-ffserver --enable-swscale --disable-network --disable-debug --disable-amd3dnow --disable-amd3dnowext --disable-ssse3 --disable-zlib --disable-bzlib

- Run make and copy the libavcodec.a, libavformat.a, libavutil.a and
  libswscale.a files to ext/exif/bin.macx.

Windows:
- Make sure MinGW and MSYS are installed and start a MinGW bash shell.

- Extract the libexif sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- Make sure MinGW and MSYS are installed and start a MinGW bash shell.

- Configure ffmpeg using:
  ./configure --disable-ffmpeg --disable-ffplay --disable-ffprobe --disable-ffserver --enable-swscale --disable-network --disable-debug --enable-memalign-hack --enable-mmx --enable-sse --disable-amd3dnow --disable-amd3dnowext --disable-ssse3 --disable-zlib --disable-bzlib --extra-cflags="-D_ISOC99_SOURCE -D_POSIX_C_SOURCE=200112 -march=i686 -mmmx -msse -msse2 -mfpmath=sse"

- Run mingw32-make and copy the libavcodec.a, libavformat.a, libavutil.a and
  libswscale.a files to ext/ffmpeg/bin.win32.
